gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bulls 125, Warriors 122
gameRecap.excerpt: Chicago defeats Golden State, 125-122. For Chicago, Nikola Vucevic led the way with a season-high 33 points, 11 rebounds, and five assists while DeMar DeRozan added 33 points, eight rebounds, and four assists in the victory. Klay Thompson tallied 25 points and two steals with Jonathan Kuminga notching the double-double with (19 points, 10 rebounds) and Draymond Green getting the triple-double (11 points, 10 rebounds, 12 assists) for Golden State in the losing effort. Chicago improves to 31-32 on the season, while Golden State moves to 33-29 with the loss.
